title: For Sale:  Sig Sauer 556r (7.62x39) w/ many extras and ammo
postcontent:
Regretfully selling one of my absolute favorite rifles I've ever owned. Awhile back I started making the transition from the AK47 to the Ar15/M4 platform, and this Sig was my last holdout. But, it's time for us to part ways as I have another project I want to work on and I have too many firearms as it is. 

Up for grabs is a gently Gen 2 (not to be confused with the GEN 1) Sig Sauer 556r semi-automatic rifle. It is chambered in 7.62x39 (AK-47 round) and is very different from any other 556r you have probably ever seen before. 

This rifle was a custom build right from the start. At the factory, Sig added an optional aluminum quad-rail instead of the cheap looking plastic hand guard that typically comes on these rifles. I then went to work on it, adding various cosmetic/functional upgrades from top to bottom. Here is a list of everything that was added:

- Factory installed Aluminum quad rail ($199 upgrade option and worth every penny)
- Burris Fastfire III reflex red dot sight w/ Q.D. picatinny mount ($225) - currently zeroed at 50 yards.
- Single point sling adaptor and sling ($50)
- LWRC 'Rail Skin' rail protectors ($40)
- Front and Rear MagPul flip up B.U.Sights ($90) - Currently zeroed at 50 yards and perfectly co-witnessed with the Burris optic
- AIM Aluminum forward grip w/ Q3 Cree LED weapons light ($75) - 200 lumens if I remember right
- Additional 3 pack of rail protectors ($30)
- 10 total TAPCO 30 round magazines ($200) - all but 3 are brand new, unused
- BlackHawk Tactical soft carry case with ample room for magazines, slings, etc. 
- 2,000 rounds of Hollow Point and Soft Point ammo ($500) - made by Wolf, all are the polymer coated kind for better performance. Non-corrosive and recent production.

*Also comes with the original box (including manual, lock, etc.), and a LIFETIME WARRANTY from Sig.

Overall, this rifle is used, but in excellent condition. I shot about 750 rounds through it and cleaned it after each use; it is barely broke in. Sig rates these rifles at around 40,000 rounds before servicing is recommended. It uses the extremely dependable gas piston system and has the Swiss style folding stock for tight spaces or other tactical needs. THIS IS THE FERRARI OF AK-47's. Clean lines, aggressive feel, and performs even better than it looks. 

I have nearly $3000 wrapped up in this package as it sits. I am giving it away at $2300. This is extremely fair for everything you are getting in this package. I cannot say enough how awesome this rifle is to shoot, own, and look at. 

To purchase, you must be 18 with a valid ID. FTF only, no shipping. I prefer to deal with CHL/CCW owners (like myself), but no required. 
I am not looking to, or interested in, splitting up this package up. Please don't ask me how much for just the ammo, the magazines, etc. Lowballer’s need not waste your time or mine. I know what this is worth, and if you know what it is, then you know what its worth as well. 

Thanks for looking.

title: For Sale:  Sig Sauer 556r (7.62x39) w/ many extras and ammo
postcontent:
Regretfully selling one of my absolute favorite rifles I've ever owned. Awhile back I started making the transition from the AK47 to the Ar15/M4 platform, and this Sig was my last holdout. But, it's time for us to part ways as I have another project I want to work on and I have too many firearms as it is. 

Up for grabs is a gently Gen 2 (not to be confused with the GEN 1) Sig Sauer 556r semi-automatic rifle. It is chambered in 7.62x39 (AK-47 round) and is very different from any other 556r you have probably ever seen before. 

This rifle was a custom build right from the start. At the factory, Sig added an optional aluminum quad-rail instead of the cheap looking plastic hand guard that typically comes on these rifles. I then went to work on it, adding various cosmetic/functional upgrades from top to bottom. Here is a list of everything that was added:

- Factory installed Aluminum quad rail ($199 upgrade option and worth every penny)
- Burris Fastfire III reflex red dot sight w/ Q.D. picatinny mount ($225) - currently zeroed at 50 yards.
- Single point sling adaptor and sling ($50)
- LWRC 'Rail Skin' rail protectors ($40)
- Front and Rear MagPul flip up B.U.Sights ($90) - Currently zeroed at 50 yards and perfectly co-witnessed with the Burris optic
- AIM Aluminum forward grip w/ Q3 Cree LED weapons light ($75) - 200 lumens if I remember right
- Additional 3 pack of rail protectors ($30)
- 10 total TAPCO 30 round magazines ($200) - all but 3 are brand new, unused
- BlackHawk Tactical soft carry case with ample room for magazines, slings, etc. 
- 2,000 rounds of Hollow Point and Soft Point ammo ($500) - made by Wolf, all are the polymer coated kind for better performance. Non-corrosive and recent production.

*Also comes with the original box (including manual, lock, etc.), and a LIFETIME WARRANTY from Sig.

Overall, this rifle is used, but in excellent condition. I shot about 750 rounds through it and cleaned it after each use; it is barely broke in. Sig rates these rifles at around 40,000 rounds before servicing is recommended. It uses the extremely dependable gas piston system and has the Swiss style folding stock for tight spaces or other tactical needs. THIS IS THE FERRARI OF AK-47's. Clean lines, aggressive feel, and performs even better than it looks. 

I have nearly $3000 wrapped up in this package as it sits. I am giving it away at $2300. This is extremely fair for everything you are getting in this package. I cannot say enough how awesome this rifle is to shoot, own, and look at. 

To purchase, you must be 18 with a valid ID. FTF only, no shipping. I prefer to deal with CHL/CCW owners (like myself), but no required. 
I am not looking to, or interested in, splitting up this package up. Please don't ask me how much for just the ammo, the magazines, etc. Lowballer’s need not waste your time or mine. I know what this is worth, and if you know what it is, then you know what its worth as well. 

Thanks for looking.

postcontent:
I received this rifle as part of a trade and don't need it. I already have a good deer rifle and this would just become a safe queen. It's a great looking gun and would probably be a good bush gun with the shorter barrel, that's just not really my style. Or maybe something to seal up and bury in the back yard if you're worried about someone taking your guns.

I don't know much history on it other than it appears to be something like a Lee-Enfield No. 1 Mk. 3 receiver with a newer Remington 30-40 Krag barrel and a nice stock. It is really comfortable to hold up against your cheek. Also, it uses an internal magazine instead of an external magazine. I have two rounds left in the box of ammo that came with it. The previous owner also painted the sights for higher contrast, though they could have done a little neater job with it. It's a solid gun for a small price. If you want more pictures of anything specific feel free to ask. I realize as a collector piece this thing isn't anything special since it's not original, but its a solid and good looking rifle for someone wanting something to shoot.
